==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pyrosome
<hw>Pyr"o*some</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Pyro-</ets> +
<ets>-some</ets> body.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any compound
ascidian of the genus <gen>Pyrosoma</gen>. The pyrosomes form large
hollow cylinders, sometimes two or three feet long, which swim at the
surface of the sea and are very phosphorescent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pyrosulphate</ent>⟦br⟧
